About this item

  • CRUISE CONTROL--Power scooters for adults has a cruise control function. After you have been riding at a steady speed for 8 seconds, the cruise control function can be activated, so that you can ride comfortably and effortlessly. Any acceleration and braking operation can exit this function.
  • 8.5 INCH LARGE TIRES--Large wheels enhance vibration filtering, adult scooter electric equipped with 8.5 inch honeycomb Solid Tire, no need to maintenance,repair,The most important is that you don't need to worry about the tire being punctured, saving the cost of tire maintenance.
  • 350W MOTOR( Peak 700W)--High power brushless motor, peak power 1000W, provides a maximum speed of 19 MPH, load capacity of the escooter electric for adults is 265 lbs, 20% uphill climb keep you motivated when going uphill.
  • 281WH BATTERY--281WH lithium-ion battery, built-in intelligent BMS system, the foldable scooter for adults provides 19 mph maximum speed and 22 miles of range.Five-hour fast charge time.
  • APP--Simply connect Electric Scooters app to lock your scooter, to customized speed and cruise control unique to APP. It works with both iPhones and Android smartphones.
  • NOTE: --This electric scooter can be ridden without the APP. The APP only provides more functions, but it does not mean that you cannot use the electric scooter without it.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

5 out of 5 stars
Zippy commuter with a few bumps
Just took this electric scooter for a spin and it's been quite the ride. That 500W motor is no joke, zipped up hills I used to dread on my old kick scooter. The 10-inch tires handle bumpy sidewalks like a champ, way smoother than I expected. That double suspension is nice, didn't feel like my teeth were chattering over every crack. The app control is pretty slick, being able to lock it from my phone gives some peace of mind. Now for the slightly less smooth bits - while it's powerful, it's also pretty heavy. Might be a struggle carrying it up stairs if you live in a walk-up. The battery life is good but not quite the full 22 miles if you're really pushing it. The folding mechanism is sturdy but can be a bit stiff, takes some muscle to collapse it. It's great for commuting but might be overkill if you're just scooting around the block. If you're looking to ditch public transit or just want a fun way to get around town, this scooter could be worth a ride. It's definitely made my commute more enjoyable, even if it's not quite as portable as I'd hoped. Great for urban dwellers or anyone with a medium-distance commute. While it might not replace a car for everyone, it's certainly upped my personal transportation game. This little electric stallion has turned my dreaded commute into a more fun and efficient trip, most of the time anyway.​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​

  • Stephen Robinson
    4.0 out of 5 stars Not a bad entry level scooter. The solid tires make it a rough ride
    Reviewed in the United States on December 4, 2024
    Style: 8.5 Inch-YellowAmazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? )
    This review is for the Qualay K078L model with 8.5" wheels and the 350W motor. It's advertised to go up to 19MPH and carry up to 265lb.

    This was nicely packed and the instructions for set up were very simple. There are 4 screws at the head of the steering shaft for mounting the handlebar. Flip the steering shaft up and lock it in place. You're about ready to go.

    Power on the screen with a long press and you have a nice display of your speed in MPH, charge using 5 bars, and which mode you are in. S, Eco or D. A double click will change your mode on the fly. A single short click will turn on your lights, including a rear red light and a front headlight. Likewise a single click will turn off your lights and a long single press will power it down.

    It's reasonably peppy off the line and easy to control. I've only used the 'S' sport mode. I want maximum speed. It claims it can get to 19MPH in one advertisement and 22MPH in another section, so I'm not sure what t he real claim is. I was able to get to 20MPH on a downhill but on the flat, the best I could get was 16MPH. This would be plenty for most city situations.

    The brakes are through a front disc brake as well as regenerative energy recovery. I found the brakes very responsive. In fact be careful not to over brake. Letting off the accelerator will engage the energy recovery and also flash your brake light warning anyone behind that you are slowing.

    I was not interested in pairing to my phone. This is just for jaunts around my neighborhood so I don't need cruise control.

    I found the 8.5 Inches wheels are smaller than I'm used to and lead to a rougher ride. Add to that, the tires are non-pneumatic. They do though have cutouts in the tires that give them a little bit of give. Overall, it's very hard riding compared to my other scooter which has larger 10" pneumatic tires. To be expected.

    For storage/carrying position, the handles fold down with a quick latch and they clip to the back of the scooter to form a carrying handle. The only issue with this is the clip that connects to the back is offset to the left hand handlebar. This makes the bar run on an angle and is not as convenient for carrying over if it was centered.

    There were a couple of quality items I noticed on arrival. One of the rubber screw covers was missing from the rear fender and the integrated bell did not work, or worked only when it wanted to.

    I found the road clearance to be an issue as well. Again this in comparison to my other scooter with 10" wheels. With the 10" pneumatic, I can wheelie up a round curb no problem. Not with the 8.5" wheels. There were a few other things I disliked about this scooter. The frame seems smaller front to back. The control cables and wiring run in and out of the tubing to reach the front wheel from the tube. It's less clean than others that run entirely inside of the tube through the hinge connection at the front of the board/bottom of the steering tube.

    Overall it's not a bad scooter and could work for many. That takes into account the price. But, for another $50 I would buy one with the 10" pneumatic tires at least. There's just no comparison in the ride comfort
    Read more

    Reviewed in the United States on September 18, 2024

    The screws to attach the handles are t15 and they used 4 screws, but in the week of owning it I’ve already tightened them so many times they are now stripped and almost defective. All main screws need to be baby sat and attended before each ride in my honest opinion, I’ve been riding it and they break loose and the wheel position changes and unalignes with the handles. Like a cheap scooter would, the parts that can’t be tightened right where it spins is also loose and that can’t be changed at all, it can push forward and backward giving to much room to move, hence the screws coming loose 24/7. Battery life is great no complaints I only use sport mode max speed is 15mph for there cheaper one. Brakes are insanely touchy and randomly grip the disc brake to hard and sLAM you to a stop, begins to wear you out quicker than I expected. Definitely recommend dual breaking for anyone in a city! Don’t even risk it on some of these hills very sporadic, works fine, but sporadic. Good beginner scooter if you’re fine with possibly locktite/permantly installing the screws, due to maintenance I don’t like that idea. One star because other scooters for less do not suffer these little problems. Hope they update there screw design to think about the shock and vibration levels those screws go through 😅

About this Item

  • CRUISE CONTROL--Power scooters for adults has a cruise control function. After you have been riding at a steady speed for 8 seconds, the cruise control function can be activated, so that you can ride comfortably and effortlessly. Any acceleration and braking operation can exit this function.
  • 8.5 INCH LARGE TIRES--Large wheels enhance vibration filtering, adult scooter electric equipped with 8.5 inch honeycomb Solid Tire, no need to maintenance,repair,The most important is that you don't need to worry about the tire being punctured, saving the cost of tire maintenance.
  • 350W MOTOR( Peak 700W)--High power brushless motor, peak power 1000W, provides a maximum speed of 19 MPH, load capacity of the escooter electric for adults is 265 lbs, 20% uphill climb keep you motivated when going uphill.
  • 281WH BATTERY--281WH lithium-ion battery, built-in intelligent BMS system, the foldable scooter for adults provides 19 mph maximum speed and 22 miles of range.Five-hour fast charge time.
  • APP--Simply connect Electric Scooters app to lock your scooter, to customized speed and cruise control unique to APP. It works with both iPhones and Android smartphones.
  • NOTE: --This electric scooter can be ridden without the APP. The APP only provides more functions, but it does not mean that you cannot use the electric scooter without it.
